Title : Marvinci
Text : [[File:Викиекспедиција Бојмија 195.jpg|300px|thumb|right|Part of the village Marvinci]]

'''Marvinci''' ([[Macedonian language|Macedonian]] and {{lang-sr-cyr|Марвинци}}) is a village in the [[Valandovo]] municipality, in the southeastern part of the [[Republic of North Macedonia]].

==Geography==
Marvinci is located in the southeast of the country, some 8&nbsp;km from the nearest town, also the municipal seat, Valandovo. The village is located in the historical region of [[Bojmija]], in the valley of the [[Vardar (river)|Vardar]], near 70 m above sea level. The surroundings of the village is plain and fertile agricultural area.

The climate is [[Humid continental climate|humid continental]], with notable influence of the [[Aegean Sea|Aegean]] (hot summers).

==Population==
According to the 2002 census, the village had a total of 504 inhabitants, out of which a majority declared as [[Serbs]] (56%), the rest as [[Slavic Macedonians|Macedonians]] (44%).<ref>[http://www.stat.gov.mk/pdf/kniga_13.pdf 2002 census results] in English and Macedonian (PDF)</ref> The predominant religion of the population is [[Eastern Orthodoxy]].

